				<wikidot:authorName>sometaters</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1355590</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I feel like with more than 100,000 images, there should be more than just less than 4,000 deaths. I could see the team taking only 1 day if all of the images are hosted on the same website, but the event describes it as a random website capable of hosting images every time. Sure, there are only so many image hosting sites but to comb through more than 100,000 sounds like it should take more 3,000-4,000 lives and a day.</p> <p>Just my nitpick. Everything else seems good. Still upvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
