				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2305705#post-3215158</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2305705/scp-3078#post-3215158</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 13 Jul 2017 14:25:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Scorpion451</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1918720</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The Neutralized classification basically means that they're monitoring the situation to make sure it's really dead, sort of like a quarantine period. If they knew for a fact that no further instances were going to appear, then it could be retired as an SCP- but for now, it's neutralized. This one's interesting in that it went from keter to neutralized almost immediately<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-727667-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup>, but compare <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2601">SCP-2601</a> for another look at neutralized as an important object class on a slower scale.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-727667-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. it probably never even had a formal file as a Keter, since it all happened in the course of a few hours</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
